WHO   — CHOANOFLAGELLATES — a life-science sphere — the brainless mind
WHAT  — A single cell with a whipping tail ringed by a collar — the humblest of microbes, and the closest living relative of every animal that has ever lived. In the choanoflagellate we see the doorstep we all crossed: the lone cell that, prompted by a bacterium, learns to gather into a colony. The threshold between one and many.
WHERE — intelligence without a brain  Framework inputs: the living; the rule; the signal; the open question  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
